BIG BANGIN’ LIFE UPDATE! Now that I have your attention, I’m happy to announce that this giant dork is moving to Los Angeles!

I love Washington with all my heart, but I’ve been here my entire life and I’m ready for something new. I will still be with @evilgeniuses doing content with their pro players in our LA studio, but there are also SO MANY things I want to do creatively and people I wanna work with that require me to move there too! I’ve been pretty lonely these last few years here and too comfortable with where I’m at, so I’m excited to see what a new city brings for me 🥺💕 and hello STAND UP COMEDY?? I cannot believe I’ll be living in the city I’ve dreamed of performing in! I know I’m taking a huge risk and it won’t be easy, but god it’s so worth it. Regardless if it works out or not, I’m instantly happier just making this decision🥰

I still have a few months before I move, so if you want to hang out or book me on your shows (please book me on your shows), hit me up! I will also be back in the area pretty often for work and family too 🐒

doing what I do best: turning a selfie into a trauma dump.

shit has been real rough lately: the last few months have been a roller coaster of questioning my worth as a creator and comedian, feeling extremely unattractive, and having anxiety about moving across state the first time. 
I’m very excited for this life change, but the anxiety and stress has kept me from really relaxing and taking care of myself, so tonight is the first time in months I’ve had the energy to dress up, put on make up, and go out since the beginning of the year. 

Idk if anyone even cares about what I just wrote, but tonight was the first time I felt really good about myself in a long time 🥺💕 big shout out to @tayafk for going on a nice date with me. you really have no idea how much that meant!

this was the first apartment I’ve ever lived in alone and it blossomed into such a beautiful, cozy home for my cats, my plants, and myself. 2 years of waking up everyday to a safe space with beautiful views that I will miss dearly ❤️

I’ll miss falling asleep to the rain, walking around this cute little downtown, and seeing my wonderful dragon friend Erasmus every morning. it’s crazy how emotional I’m getting about all this but I’m very excited to finally have a fresh start somewhere new

goodbye for now Washington 🥲

it’s been 2 years since I started working at @evilgeniuses! It’s been a wild year; from endlessly meeting and working with some of the coolest, most talented people in gaming, to moving across state to produce fun stuff in our LA office! I’m grateful for all the wonderful friendships and opportunities I’ve had these last couple years and looking forward to starting fresh in a new city and working with the LA crew! shout out to @tothelapointe for putting up with me another year ❤️

I’ve officially been living/performing in LA for 3 months now! although my reasons for moving here were more personal than career driven, I’ve been blessed with some incredible opportunities in this short period that I’m extremely proud of and made me want work harder (and funnier!) at comedy ❤️

this move was one of the best decisions I’ve ever made, but it’s been hard on me. I’m still adapting to my new environment and schedule, while trying to see more shows and make more friends in the scene… but whenever I’m tough on myself for not “grinding” enough for networking and stage time, I look back at the few months I’ve been here and realize that I’m still killing it! In the 9 years I’ve been performing stand up comedy (off/on lol), this is the happiest and most excited I’ve ever been on stage. thank you everyone who has given this city newbie stage time, I cannot wait for more ❤️

FINALLY, the reveal is here! my complete Bloodborne/Dark Souls 3 back piece by the incredible @themildginger 

8 brutal sessions, just as brutal as playing the games 😂 I’m so happy with how this turned out and I’m absolutely speechless by her design, linework, placement, etc. (she even placed the lamp flame over my birthmark so it looks like it burned my skin which is SO COOL). I have a lot of great tattoos but this one is just UNBELIEVABLE! 

I’m so glad we were able to finish this piece before both of our big moves 🥲 If you’re in PA and need a tattoo, please check out Amanda’s work. She’s incredibly talented and I’m proud to have both of back AND my full Zelda sleeve done by her 🖤

If you told me back in January that by the end of 2023, I would moved out of my hometown for the first time to a brand new state, sell out headlining gigs, make an insane amount of new friends in gaming and comedy, feed elephants in Thailand, take my 5th trip to Japan, see Blink 182 live again, go to red carpet events, AND lose my job?? I would’ve only believed the last part 🙃

2023 was wild as hell. I may be unemployed and slowly running out of money, but somehow this is the happiest I’ve been in years. Looking forward to being broke and thriving in 2024 🥰

📷: @justoffthesix
